Hi everyone. Yesterday, we reimaged our roborio to the 2024 image. When trying Phoenix Tuner (v1.9.4.1), the roborio connects, but we get no CAN devices listed.
We’ve tried going to http://172.22.11.2:1250/?action=getdevices, but the site refuses to connect. We also tried using Phoenix Tuner X, but CAN devices still don’t connect.
Here are a few screenshots:

image (2)1920×1057 366 KB

image (3)1920×1019 110 KB

Any help in fixing this is appreciated.

You need to either deploy the temporary diagnostic server, or run a 2024 robot project with the Phoenix vendordep installed and initialize a device.

Additionally, Tuner v1 will NOT work for the temporary diagnostic server, plus it’s been removed from our installer. You should be using Tuner X which is installed via the Google Play Store, or the Microsoft Store for device configuration.

Your computer likely doesn’t have a valid connection to the roboRIO. If you are connecting over USB, ensure you have the Driver Station installed (it installs the roboRIO USB drivers).

If you are connecting over wireless, you’ll need to change the IP/Team Number box to your team number, ensure Tuner has a green “ping” (first bubble in the box in the middle of the screen), then deploy the diagnostic server.
